[It is not specifically stated that a strain of enterohemorrhagic _E. coli_ was involved here but with the bloody diarrhea, it is most certainly the case.

This cluster is not related to the ongoing romaine lettuce-associated EHEC outbreak. Day care centers can be sites for person-to-person transmission clusters of a variety of enteric illnesses such as EHEC rather than the cluster being entirely food-related. Indeed, in most outbreaks, secondary household-related transmission of EHEC occurs.

Moore, Oklahoma is located in the central part of this Midwestern USA state and can be found on a map at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moore,_Oklahoma. - Mod.LL

